    "en": {
      "title": "2026 Twenty20 World Cup co-hosted by Sri Lanka and India",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The International Cricket Council (ICC) has announced the future tournaments for 2023-27. These future tournaments have been announced along with the World Cup to be held in India next year, and five major tournaments have been announced.",
        "Thus, the T20 World Cup to be held in 2026 will be co-hosted by India and Sri Lanka.",
        "India, Bangladesh and Sri Lanka co-hosted the 2011 50-over World Cup.",
        "According to the 2023-2027 future tournament plan, the ICC 777 international matches will be played between the 12 main member countries. 173 Test matches, 281 ODI matches and 323 T20 matches will be held accordingly.",
        "During this period, there will be an ODI World Cup, a Champion's Tournament, two T20 World Cup tournaments and the World Test Championship.",
        "West Indies and USA will host the T20 World Cup in 2024 and Pakistan will host the Champions Trophy in 2025.",
        "India and Sri Lanka will co-host the T20 World Cup in 2026, while South Africa, Zimbabwe and Namibia will host the Cricket World Cup in 2027."
      ],
